# Builder product guideline (always)

When changing the team page builder, blocks, editors, WhatsApp flows, or data collection — read and follow **`docs/BUILDER_GUIDELINE.md`**.

## Quick reference

- **Layout:** 3 columns (structure nav + single editor card + live preview). See `docs/BUILDER_BASELINE_LOCK.md` — do not redesign without explicit request.
- **Blocks:** metadata in `lib/blocks/meta.ts` (essential / engagement / advanced). Empty blocks hidden on public page.
- **WhatsApp:** three modes — click-to-chat (free), share summary (free), Twilio auto-notify (optional). No two-way chat sync.
- **Data collection:** polls → `poll_votes`; roster → attendance block; payments tracker → `page_settings.payments`.
- **External services:** link/embed based (Google Calendar URL, Strava link, etc.) — not API sync.
- **Publish gate:** team name + logo required; checkout may be required when billing is configured.
- **Coach guide in UI:** `lib/builder/coach-help-content.ts` — keep in sync with `docs/BUILDER_GUIDELINE.md`; sidebar «How it works» + mobile Guide modal.
- **Academy:** hub at `/admin`, up to 20 teams, `showAcademyHub` in builder — see guideline §2.1.
- **Hero:** one `TeamHeroCard`, four CSS variants — see `team-hero-layout.mdc`.

## Do not

- Promise WhatsApp or calendar "sync" beyond click-to-chat, share text, or embed URLs.
- Add duplicate section nav or fork hero per layout variant.
- Store coach/parent data outside documented locations without updating the guideline.

## After product changes

Update `docs/BUILDER_GUIDELINE.md` in the same change when behavior, data model, or WhatsApp flows change.
